<h2>Limor&nbsp;Schafman</h2>
<h3>President<br />KeystoneTech Group</h3>
<div style="float: left;">
  <img src="http://speaker.ce.org/files/content/attendees/bio_4161_limor 300.jpg" style="margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; max-width: 275px;" alt="Limor Schafman">
</div>
<div style="margin: 10px;">
  <p><span style="font-size: 10pt">Limor believes in the Great Convergence &ndash; of digital and real worlds, of myriad technologies and of industries which were formerly in different silos &ndash; coming together to create more robust, rich, engaging experiences. As president of KTG, Limor Schafman brings business, marketing and business development acumen to technology companies from start-up to Fortune 500 seeking to enter new markets.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt">Limor shifted her career from international business attorney, working in Paris France, to marketing strategist in 1994.&nbsp; She entered the sector of digital media and entertainment technology in Los Angeles, working on the production of two full motion video games, followed by becoming director of marketing and business development for a theme park design/build company. Limor began her entrepreneurial ventures ten years ago leading and funding a team to develop a sports video game hardware peripheral/software application product. She formed the KeystoneTech Group consultancy in 2002 to use her creative, production and marketing savvy for companies starting up and expanding their business.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt">With an eye always on multi-disciplinary, cultural and international trends, she is founder and chief instigator of the Games Gateway Serious Games Meetup (Washington DC); co-founder, past president and Chair Chair of the IPv6 Forum for Israel; past president of the World Future Society D.C. Chapter, and worked with the Distributed Computing Information Association [P2P], Venture Mentors, and the Northern Virginia Technology Council.</span></p>
<div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-size: 10pt">Limor&rsquo;s work can also be found on <i>DigIn! Radio </i>(<a href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/Limor-Schafman"><font color="#0000ff">http://www.blogtalkradio.com/Limor-Schafman</font></a>) and the only technology talk show, <i>Crash Course with Limor Schafman, </i>&nbsp;(<a href="http://www.tvmainstream.com/series/crash_course"><font color="#0000ff">http://www.tvmainstream.com/series/crash_course</font></a>).&nbsp;She also authors the blog <i>DigIn! (</i><a href="http://www.diginblog.com/"><i><font color="#0000ff">www.diginblog.com</font></i></a><i>)</i>. You can also find her on Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn.</span></div>
</div>


              
